{
  "name": "Gamekeeper's Cross",
  "type": "equipment",
  "img": "Art%20-%20Items/jewelry/amulet_a_bladed_cross_made_of_wood_magic_item_dd_magic.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This 3\" diameter amulet of wood bears an inscription in varisian across the back: \"<em>They killed my uncle, the were-bear called \"Bern the Bloodsoaked.\" When they buried him, a great tree grew out of his grave within days. They chopped it down and burned it. I saved only this piece. Now for vengeance.\"</em></p><p>This item provides a number of benefits to a druid or ranger who holds it.</p><p>It acts as an amulet of Natural Armor +1.</p><p>When the wearer recieves a  @UUID[Compendium.pf1.spells.Item.la7kuehewu85ybnt]{Barkskin} spell, the amulet also casts @UUID[Compendium.pf1.spells.Item.jnlr9cuepka1l26e]{Enlarge Person} and @UUID[Compendium.pf1.spells.Item.hosf489xyoexmp57]{Longstrider}. This combined buff lasts 10 minutes per wearer level. The wearer appears to be a large werebear made entirely of enchanted oak bark. They gain two claw attacks and one bite, and can use both claw attacks on a charge as if they have the Pounce feat.</p><img src=\"Art%20-%20Items/jewelry/amulet_a_bladed_cross_made_of_wood_magic_item_dd_magic.png\" />",
      "instructions": "",
      "unidentified": "<p>Weird little wooden amulet.</p>"
    },
